node.text: Wow lupus. It takes a lot of courage even just to talk about this shit to a bunch of strangers who maybe follow you only for for your ferrari and rollsroyce (like me). So good to hear that you're in remission

May is Lupus awareness month and yesterday was World Lupus Day 💜 
For those of us suffering with Lupus or any kind of underlying illness, it has been a harrowing couple of months. We have had to endure lockdowns and the fear of contracting Covid-19. Lupus sufferers have over-active, compromised immune systems which make us more susceptible to infections. If we do contract Covid-19, our symptoms are more likely to be severe. So for those living with illness, I pray you stay safe and find what works for you, especially at this time. 
There is no cure for this chronic condition but I’m happy to say that I’m in a good place and in remission! It took a lot of patience to get here and I am proud to be a #lupuswarrior. 
Ps: I didn’t have the courage to post the 2nd photo of me going through chemo, as is. So I hid it behind a random photo of myself 😅

#lupus #lupusawareness #lupusawarenessmonth #worldlupusday #sgunited #stayhomesg
